PROJECT RULES — Materna360Oficial

Tech & tooling
- Framework: Next.js 14 (App Router, src/app).
- Language: TypeScript.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (+ tailwind.config).
- Icons: lucide-react.
- Animations: Framer Motion (subtle, premium feel).
- Package manager: npm (use `npm ci` in CI/Builder).
- Node: 20.x (match Vercel setting).

Structure & paths
- Keep the App Router in `src/app`.
- Shared components live in `components/` (subfolders: `components/ui`, `components/features`).
- Path alias is `@/*` (do NOT switch to `src/*`).
- Do not duplicate pages or move files out of `src/app` without strong reason.

Dev server & scripts
- Dev server runs on http://localhost:3000.
- `scripts.dev` must be `next dev -p 3000`.
- When the Builder needs deps, run `npm ci` (not `npm install`) unless `ci` fails.

Branching & PRs
- Default working branch: `stellar-den`. Open PRs **from `stellar-den` into `main`**.
- Mark PRs as **Draft** by default.
- Use Conventional Commits (e.g., `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`).
- Do not change repository or create new ones.

Design guidelines
- Keep a “premium” look: soft shadows, rounded corners, smooth micro-interactions.
- Respect the brand palette (Primary: #ff005e; Secondary: #ffd8e6).
- Ensure mobile-first responsiveness and a11y (focus states, readable contrast).

What NOT to change
- Do not rename the project or packages arbitrarily.
- Do not alter `@/*` alias, `tsconfig.json` baseUrl/paths, or the port 3000.
- Do not hardcode secrets; use `.env` with existing var names.
- Do not introduce breaking changes to API routes or Next config.

Deliverables expectations
- When adding screens (e.g., “Meu Dia”, “Cuidar”, “Descobrir”, “Eu360”), keep the bottom tab bar consistent.
- Use reusable UI atoms from `components/ui` and compose features in `components/features`.
- Add subtle motion (opacity/translate/scale) and consistent shadow tokens per Tailwind config.
